text: Decent taste but extremely pricy. $5.30. The signboard misleading, stated $3.50 for fishball noodles.

At silent hours (4am), the time they take to prepare the meal, my grandmother could complete a 2.4km sprint. (Via delivery which shouldnt be long due to the hour I ordered and traffic condition) Which boils to one thing. Vendor issues. Either lazy or could not be bothered
